  <bioghist id="aspace_390726ff7ebda0ad87469bba541cdbeb">
    <head>ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY</head>
<p>Lake Mohonk Mountain House is a resort hotel in the Shawangunk Mountains near New Paltz, New York, owned and operated by the Smileys, a Quaker family. Albert Smiley bought a tavern near Lake Mohonk and 280 acres, including the lake, in 1869.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_972fbe4516b1f64e3206145e9873f3eb">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Letters and letterbooks, including house correspondence, Smiley and Benjamin S. Helmer correspondence; bills and bank statements; employee time books and payrolls; insurance policies; guest accounts and ledgers. Also includes records and accounts concerning provisions and maintenance, workman's compensation and unemployment, the golf course and tennis courts, dining room, laundry, and power house. Also, Brook Farm and Spring Farm cattle and milk production records, guest records and correspondence.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_55144cd6864776be49e6e521b1c6ddbb">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Lake Mohonk Mountain House records, #2835. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
